## No Intermediaries (94)

A verse that strips everything back:

> *"You have come to Us alone, just as We created you the first time, and you have left behind what We bestowed on you."* (94)

This is addressed to each person on Judgment Day. You arrive alone. No wealth, no family, no status, and no idols or intermediaries to speak on your behalf. Just you and God. Everything you relied on in this world is gone.

The Meccans believed their idols could *intercede* for them with God, put in a good word, act as go-betweens. This verse says: on that day, there are no go-betweens. You face God directly.

